From: johnblue <dev@johnblue>
Date: Mon, 1 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 1/1] hw/i2c+arm: add MCTP-over-SMBus endpoint and ast2600-johnblue machine

Adds a new QEMU I2C slave device (mctp-i2c-endpoint) that implements
DSP0237 MCTP-over-SMBus framing, DSP0236 MCTP Control (EID assignment),
DSP0240 PLDM Base (Type 0), and DSP0248 PLDM PMC (Type 2) with two
simulated sensors (CPU temperature=42C, 12V rail=11.98V).

Also registers "ast2600-johnblue" machine that places the endpoint on
I2C bus 1 at address 0x0f, matching meta-johnblue DTS patch and
mctp-setup-i2c.service.

Upstream-Status: Pending [Not submitted upstream — QEMU device model for OpenBMC development]
Signed-off-by: johnblue <dev@johnblue>
---
